calculate TPM

TPM = transcripts per kilobase million TPM = (num reads / (geneLength/1000)) / (total RPK for sample / 1000000)

read_counts_norm <- read_coverage_wide[,-c(1,2)]

sample_counts <- tibble(sample=colnames(read_counts_norm),
                        viral_read_counts=colSums(read_counts_norm))
read_counts_norm <- t(read_counts_norm)

collapse replicates from Dot’s study

“%>%” allows you to “pipe” different functions. For instance this, loads the “merged” dataframe, then processes it to collapse sequencing replicates. In the Dai et al (2020) study, the authors took multiple sequencing replicates for every sample that they took. For the analyses we’ll be doing, we want to collapse these techincal replicates into one sample. We could have also done this before mapping the reads to the contigs.

abund_table <- merged %>%

  summarize(
